  "title": "Nvidia Q3 2025 Earnings Call",
  "datetime": "2025-11-19T21:00:00Z",
  "period": "CY2025_Q3",
  "location": "Santa Clara, CA",
  "url": "https://investor.nvidia.com/",
  "turns": [
    {
      "speaker_id": "jensen-huang",
      "speaker_name": "Jensen Huang",
      "speaker_role": "CEO",
      "timestamp": "00:01:00",
      "text": "Q3 data center revenue was $53.2 billion, up 102% year-over-year — the first time in history a semiconductor company has generated over $50 billion in a single segment in a quarter. Automotive revenue crossed $1 billion for the first time, driven by our DRIVE platform adoption at 15 OEMs. We are previewing Rubin, our next-generation architecture, which we expect to begin shipping in Q2 2026. Rubin will deliver 3x the training performance of Blackwell per rack."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "colette-kress",
      "speaker_name": "Colette Kress",
      "speaker_role": "CFO",
      "timestamp": "00:18:00",
      "text": "Total revenue was $58.8 billion, up 94% year-over-year. Gross margin was 74.8%. Operating income was $41.5 billion with an operating margin of 70.6%. We generated $32.1 billion in free cash flow. For Q4, we expect revenue of $62 billion, plus or minus 2%, with gross margin of approximately 73%."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "operator",
      "speaker_name": "Operator",
      "speaker_role": "Operator",
      "timestamp": "00:38:00",
      "text": "Our next question comes from Ben Reitzes at Melius Research."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "analyst-ben-reitzes",
      "speaker_name": "Ben Reitzes",
      "speaker_role": "Analyst",
      "timestamp": "00:38:20",
      "text": "Jensen, Rubin at 3x Blackwell performance per rack — does the cadence of annual architecture releases concern hyperscalers who are building long-term infrastructure, or does it accelerate their purchasing given upgrade economics?"
    }
  ],
